-- Anglo American shares up in South Africa, CEO to step down
-- 
-- Fri Oct 26, 2012 3:25am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/26/us-safrica-angloamerican-idUSBRE89P0A520121026

 

 JOHANNESBURG  (Reuters) - Shares of Anglo American ( AGLJ.J ) rose by more than 2 percent in South Africa on Friday after Chief Executive Cynthia Carroll said she would be stepping down. 
 Shares opened 2.3 percent higher at 268.50, outperforming a 0.37 percent drop by the Johannesburg bourse's blue-chip index  .JTOPI . (Reporting by  Helen Nyambura-Mwaura ; Editing by  Jon Herskovitz )